• A virus is a self-replicating program that produces its own copy by attaching itself to another program , computer boot sector or document. 
• Viruses are transmitted through file downloads , infected disk/flash drives and from email attachments 
• Indications of virus attacks : 
	○ Constant antivirus alerts 
	○ Suspicious hard drive 
	○ Lack of storage space 
	○ Unwanted pop-up windows. 
• Charcteristics of viruses : 
	○ Infects other program 
	○ Transform intself 
	○ Encryptes itself 
	○ Alters data 
	○ Corrupts files and programs 
	○ Replicates itself 
• Stages of Virus Lifecycle : 
	○ Design : Development of virus code using programming language or construction kits 
	○ Replication : the virus replicates for a period within the target system and then spreads itself 
